---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PrimaryCTA from '../components/PrimaryCTA.astro';
import LinkedInIcon from '../components/icons/LinkedInIcon.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "name": "Daniel Grainger",
  "url": "https://ranking-atlas.com/about",
  "jobTitle": "Founder",
  "worksFor": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Ranking Atlas",
    "url": "https://ranking-atlas.com"
  },
  "description": "Founder of Ranking Atlas. Applies research methodology to citation equity for B2B SaaS brands.",
  "sameAs": [
    "https://www.linkedin.com/in/daniel-grainger/",
    "https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/eth.12280"
  ]
};
---

<Layout
  title="About — Ranking Atlas"
  description="Ranking Atlas is an editorial PR agency for B2B SaaS brands. We run fixed-price campaigns that earn editorial coverage on authoritative publishers, building the citation equity that puts brands in AI answers."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-16 pb-12 md:pt-20 md:pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-3 text-[#64748B]">Our Story</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-[1.1] mb-6">
        About Ranking Atlas
      </h1>
      <p class="text-body text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed">
        Ranking Atlas is an editorial PR agency for B2B SaaS brands. We run fixed-price campaigns that earn editorial coverage on authoritative publishers, building the citation equity that puts brands in AI answers. Think of it as PageRank for AI.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Founded on Research Principles -->
  <section class="py-8 md:py-10 bg-bg-cream">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6">
        Founded on Research Principles
      </h2>

      <!-- Float-based founder intro -->
      <figure class="md:float-left md:mr-8 md:mb-2 mb-5 flex flex-col items-start">
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/daniel-grainger/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <img
            src="/assets/images/author/daniel-headshot.jpg"
            alt="Daniel Grainger, founder of Ranking Atlas"
            class="w-32 h-32 md:w-36 md:h-36 rounded-full object-cover shadow-card"
            width="144"
            height="144"
          />
        </a>
        <figcaption class="mt-3 text-sm leading-tight">
          <div class="font-semibold text-ink">Daniel Grainger</div>
          <div class="text-[#64748B] mt-0.5">Founder, Ranking Atlas</div>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/daniel-grainger/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 mt-2 text-brand hover:text-[#4338CA] transition-colors"
          >
            <LinkedInIcon class="w-3.5 h-3.5" />
            <span>LinkedIn</span>
          </a>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <div class="space-y-3 text-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Ranking Atlas was founded by Daniel Grainger. He has spent years as a digital PR specialist, pitching journalists, building media relationships, and earning coverage on authoritative publishers for B2B brands. He is also a <a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/eth.12280" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">published scientific author</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          That combined discipline shaped how Ranking Atlas operates. Most PR agencies run on intuition: pitch a lot, see what lands, report on volume. We treat citation equity as an observable system with measurable signals. Campaigns are structured interventions. Outcomes are evidenced against data.
        </p>
        <p>
          The work respects everyone at the editorial table. Journalists deserve stories worth publishing. Readers deserve coverage worth reading. Clients deserve the citations they paid for.
        </p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-ink">
          The research discipline is the agency's foundation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="clear-both"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: How We Work -->
  <section class="py-8 md:py-10">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6">
        How We Work
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          We run every campaign as a structured intervention.
        </p>
        <p>
          We baseline a brand's citation pattern before the campaign starts. We identify the authoritative publishers AI systems cite in the client's vertical. We target editorial coverage on those publishers. We measure the citation pattern after.
        </p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-ink">
          Each step is documented. Each output is evidenced.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our published research follows the same discipline. The Cost of Authority report is built on a proprietary dataset of 140,000+ publisher listings collected over six years. The research we publish is the research we apply to client work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: What a Campaign Looks Like -->
  <section class="py-8 md:py-10 bg-bg-cream">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6">
        What a Campaign Looks Like
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Fixed-price campaigns, not retainers. Every engagement has defined scope and a guaranteed minimum number of editorial placements. If we do not hit the guarantee, we keep working until we do.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every campaign includes before-and-after AI citation measurement across ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, and Google AI Overviews. Clients see exactly how their brand's presence in AI answers shifted.
        </p>
        <p>
          We work primarily with fintech, privacy, cybersecurity, and data infrastructure SaaS companies, where the pattern of AI citation is most established.
        </p>
        <p>
          No retainers. No monthly billing. One campaign, one price, one defined outcome.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA band -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-20 text-center" style="background: #5D4FE0;">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none" style="background-image: url('data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22 width=%22100%22 height=%22100%22><filter id=%22n%22><feTurbulence type=%22fractalNoise%22 baseFrequency=%220.9%22/></filter><rect width=%22100%22 height=%22100%22 filter=%22url(%23n)%22/></svg>');"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white leading-[1.1] mb-6">
        Ready to Start a Campaign?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/80 mb-10">$3.5K per campaign. Guaranteed editorial placements on authoritative publishers. No retainers.</p>
      <PrimaryCTA href="/contact" />
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
